ABUJA – History will be made today as the state-of -the -art cycling arena, inside the Moshood Abiola Stadium, Abuja, for the first time since its construction 16 years ago, host the maiden Africa Track Cycling Championships. Eight countries namely Nigeria, Burkina Faso, Ghana, Egypt, Cote d’ Ivoire, Benin Rep. and Morocco are in Abuja for the championships. However, Mohammed Wagih Azzam, President of the Confederation of African Cycling (CAC), has commended Nigeria for finally putting the Velodrome Complex to use after 16 years of inactivity. Azzam said that with the facility, track cycling has come to stay, as he urged Nigeria to take full advantage of the arena and join the global track cycling bug. He said that Nigeria has the men and women that can launch her on the global arena, noting that natural strength of the African will always come handy. He also commended Giadomenico Massari, President of Cycling Federation of Nigeria, CAC members, Dr Emmanuel Igbinosa and Coach Mohammed Bashiru for their contributions.